The paper discusses the concept of Self-Sovereign Identity (SSI) enabled by blockchain technology, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the architecture, identifiers, authentication solutions, and verifiable claims, which are relevant to the fields of cryptography (cs.CR), databases (cs.DB), information retrieval (cs.IR), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper's focus on blockchain technology and its application to identity management makes it most likely to belong to cs.CR and cs.CY (cybersecurity and cryptography).
